        "id": "13459974",
        "author": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=acmurthy",
          "name": "acmurthy",
          "key": "acmurthy",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
          },
          "displayName": "Arun Murthy",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
        },
        "body": "Apart from the default FIFO scheduler, none of the existing schedulers in hadoop-1.x support application priority - this leads to very interesting corner cases, resource deadlocks etc. which no one yet supports.\n\nWith YARN it's much more feasible, but not yet implemented.\n\nHope that helps...",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=acmurthy",
          "name": "acmurthy",
          "key": "acmurthy",
          "avatarUrls": {
